headline.main: Astronauts Ready to Start 62-Orbit Space Trip Today; Gemini Astronauts Ready for 62-Orbit Space Trip From Cape Kennedy Today

results.snippet: CAPE KENNEDY, Fla., Thursday, June 3 -- Final preparations were pushed here early today for the start at 10 A.M. Eastern daylight time of this country's most ambitious space venture to date. Fueling was completed during the night for a 62-orbit...
results.lead_paragraph: CAPE KENNEDY, Fla., Thursday, June 3 -- Final preparations were pushed here early today for the start at 10 A.M. Eastern daylight time of this country's most ambitious space venture to date. Fueling was completed during the night for a 62-orbit flight in which, it is hoped, an orbiting rocket stage will be approached, inspected and perhaps even touched.

results.lead_paragraph: At Cape Kennedy early last Monday afternoon, workmen hoisted a giant Titan II booster into position on Pad 19 for the scheduled August launching of Gemini 5. As the rocket was being raised, Gemini 4 was speeding overhead toward splashdown in the Atlantic after a triumphal 1.6 million mile, 62-orbit journey that had begun four days earlier from the same launching pad.

results.lead_paragraph: Last week's flight of Gemini 4 and Luna 6 pointed to intensification of the Soviet-American moon race. At the same time an increasing chorus -- ranging from a Vatican magazine in Italy to a Communist newspaper in Czechoslovakia -- called for a halt to that race and its replacement by Soviet-American cooperation in space.

headline.main: 9 KILLED AS JET CRASHES AT SHOW; Paris Exhibition Goes On -- Astronauts Tour Displays

results.snippet: PARIS, June 19 -- Nine persons were killed and four injured when an Italian jet crashed into a crowded parking lot at the International Air Show today. Thousands of onlookers saw the fatal mishap, the second since the show began.
